The file is severely corrupted from line 680 onwards. The `GetConstantIntRange` lambda, which should end around line 685, is a mess of repeated code fragments. The corruption seems to end somewhere after line 700. The original lambda definition starts at line 674 and ends at line 685.

My strategy is to replace this entire corrupted block with the correct, fixed version of the lambda. I will use `sed` to delete the range from line 674 to a safe point after the corruption (I'll pick line 705 to be safe) and then insert the correct code.

Here is the correct and fixed code for the `GetConstantIntRange` lambda:
```cpp
  auto GetConstantIntRange =
      [](Value *Length,
         std::optional<int64_t> Offset) -> std::optional<ConstantRange> {
    auto *ConstantLength = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Length);
    if (ConstantLength && Offset &&
        ConstantLength->getValue().isStrictlyPositive()) {
      APInt Off(64, *Offset, true);
      APInt Sz(64, ConstantLength->getSExtValue(), true);
      APInt End;
      bool Overflow;
      End = Off.sadd_ov(Sz, Overflow);
      if (Overflow)
        return ConstantRange::getFull(64);
      return ConstantRange(Off, End);
    }
    return std::nullopt;
  };
```
I will now construct a `sed` command to perform this replacement. I'll delete from line 674 to 705 and then use the `i` (insert) command at line 674 to add the correct code.

```bash
